hpicfIpConfig.name: hpicfIpConfig

revisions.description: Added hpicfIpClientTrackerUntrusted object and hpicfIpClientTrackerTrusted object in hpicfIpClientTrackerGroup2 and deprecated hpicfIpClientTrackerGroup.
Added hpicfIpClientTrackerObjects group in hpicfIpConfigObjects for Static IP Visibility feature and added hpicfIpClientTrackerEnable object, hpicfIpConfigCompliance10 and hpicfIpClientTrackerGroup.
Added hpicfIpv6InterfaceReachableTime and hpicfIpv6InterfaceRetransmitTime objects to hpicfIpv6InterfaceTable.
Added hpicfIpv6InterfaceDadAttempts and hpicfIpv6InterfaceDadAttemptsMode object to the hpicfIpv6InterfaceTable.
Added hpicfIpv6NDDadAttempts to augment the hpicfIpv6GlobalConfigObjects.
Added hpicfIpv4InterfaceLocalProxyArp on to the hpicfIpv4InterfaceEntry.
Added hpicfIpv6InterfaceTable to augment the Ipv6InterfaceTable.
Added hpicfUdpTunnelMirrorSessionID to augment the tunnelInetConfigEntry object in RFC4087.
Added hpicfUdpTunnelSrcPort to augment the tunnelInetConfigEntry object in RFC4087.

hpicfIpConfig.contactinfo: Hewlett-Packard Company 8000 Foothills Blvd. Roseville, CA 95747
hpicfIpConfig.description: This MIB module describes objects for basic IP address configuration and interface configuration for devices in the HP Integrated Communication Facility product line.

hpicfIpAddressTable.name: hpicfIpAddressTable
hpicfIpAddressTable.description: This table contains manually configured IPv4 and IPv6 addresses for each interface. An entry in this table may not exist in the active state unless all objects in the entry are consistent. In particular, the value of hpicfIpAddressPrefixLength.

hpicfIpAddressEntry.name: hpicfIpAddressEntry
hpicfIpAddressEntry.description: An entry in the hpicfIpAddressEntry contains a single manually configured IP address.

hpicfIpAddressAddr.name: hpicfIpAddressAddr
hpicfIpAddressAddr.description: The IP address to which this entry's addressing information pertains. hpicfIpAddressAddr is always interpreted within the context of hpicfIpAddressAddrType.

hpicfIpAddressPrefixLength.name: hpicfIpAddressPrefixLength
hpicfIpAddressPrefixLength.description: The prefix length associated with IP address.

hpicfIpAddressType.name: hpicfIpAddressType
hpicfIpAddressType.description: IP address type. For V4 addresses the value will be unicast.

hpicfIpAddressRowStatus.name: hpicfIpAddressRowStatus
hpicfIpAddressRowStatus.description: The status of the IP address entry.

hpicfIpAddressExtendedType.name: hpicfIpAddressExtendedType
hpicfIpAddressExtendedType.description: IP address type. For V4 addresses the value will be none. For V6 address it can be eui64 and linkLocal also.

hpicfSwitchIpAddressTable.name: hpicfSwitchIpAddressTable
hpicfSwitchIpAddressTable.description: This read only table contains IPV4 and/or IPV6 addresses for each interface. These IP Addresses are either manually configured or obtained by a dynamic method (such as DHCP). This table will hold all manually configured IP Addresses that exist in hpicfIpAddressTable except for those entries that are not in active state (hpicfIpAddressRowStatus).

hpicfSwitchIpAddressEntry.name: hpicfSwitchIpAddressEntry
hpicfSwitchIpAddressEntry.description: An entry in the hpicfSwitchIpAddressEntry contains a single IP address.

hpicfSwitchIpAddressAddr.name: hpicfSwitchIpAddressAddr
hpicfSwitchIpAddressAddr.description: The IP address to which this entry's addressing information pertains. hpicfSwitchIpAddressAddr is always interpreted within the context of hpicfSwitchIpAddressAddrType.

hpicfSwitchIpAddressPrefixLength.name: hpicfSwitchIpAddressPrefixLength
hpicfSwitchIpAddressPrefixLength.description: The prefix length associated with IP address.

hpicfSwitchIpAddressType.name: hpicfSwitchIpAddressType
hpicfSwitchIpAddressType.description: IP address type. For V4 addresses the value will be unicast.

hpicfSwitchIpAddressStatus.name: hpicfSwitchIpAddressStatus
hpicfSwitchIpAddressStatus.description: The status of the address, describing if the address can be used for communication. In the absence of other information, an IPv4 address is always preferred(1).

hpicfSwitchIpAddressPreferredLifetime.name: hpicfSwitchIpAddressPreferredLifetime
hpicfSwitchIpAddressPreferredLifetime.reference: For IPv6 RFC2461, especially sections 2 and 4.6.2 and RFC2462
hpicfSwitchIpAddressPreferredLifetime.description: The remaining length of time in seconds that this address will continue to be preferred, i.e. time until deprecation. A value of 4,294,967,295 represents infinity. The address generated from a deprecated address should no longer be used as a source address in new communications, but packets received on such an interface are processed as expected. The default for IPv4 addresses is 4,294,967,295 (infinity).

hpicfSwitchIpAddressValidLifetime.name: hpicfSwitchIpAddressValidLifetime
hpicfSwitchIpAddressValidLifetime.reference: For IPv6 RFC2461, especially sections 2 and 4.6.2 and RFC2462
hpicfSwitchIpAddressValidLifetime.description: The remaining length of time, in seconds, that this address will continue to be valid, i.e. time until invalidation. A value of 4,294,967,295 represents infinity. The address generated from an invalidated address should not appear as the destination or source address of a packet. The default for IPv4 addresses is 4,294,967,295 (infinity).

hpicfSwitchIpAddressExtendedType.name: hpicfSwitchIpAddressExtendedType
hpicfSwitchIpAddressExtendedType.description: IP address type. For V4 addresses the value will be none. For V6 address it can be eui64 and linkLocal also.

hpicfIpNetToPhysicalPort.name: hpicfIpNetToPhysicalPort
hpicfIpNetToPhysicalPort.description: This object gives the port through which the physical address was learnt

hpicfIpNetToPhysicalTableClear.name: hpicfIpNetToPhysicalTableClear
hpicfIpNetToPhysicalTableClear.description: This provides the clear options for hpicfIpNetToPhysicalTable. A value of 2 is to clear arp table. A value of 3 is to clear the ipv6 neighbor table. A get returns 'unknown' always.

hpicfIpv4InterfaceTable.name: hpicfIpv4InterfaceTable
hpicfIpv4InterfaceTable.description: This table contains per-interface IPV4 configuration information.

hpicfIpv4InterfaceEntry.name: hpicfIpv4InterfaceEntry
hpicfIpv4InterfaceEntry.description: An entry in the hpicfIpv4InterfaceEntry contains IPV4 interface specific configuration information. This table is indexed by ipv4InterfaceIfIndex.

hpicfIpv4InterfaceDhcpEnable.name: hpicfIpv4InterfaceDhcpEnable
hpicfIpv4InterfaceDhcpEnable.description: Changing this flag to 'full' will clear any existing IP address configuration for this interface and will cause the device to use a dynamic method (e.g. DHCP) to obtain its IP configuration and other configuration parameter (such as gateway, time of day, etc...) for this interface. Setting this flag to 'inform' will allow manual IP address configuration and yet permit other configuration parameters (such as gateway, time of day, etc...) to be obtained from a DHCP server. Setting this flag to 'off' will allow manual IP configuration but disallow any DHCP configuration.

hpicfIpv4InterfaceForwarding.name: hpicfIpv4InterfaceForwarding
hpicfIpv4InterfaceForwarding.description: This flag indicates whether this interface is forwarding the datagrams that were not addressed to this interface. Setting this flag to 'enabled' (the default) results in forwarding the datagrams that were not addressed to this interface. Setting this flag to 'disabled' results in ignoring datagrams that were not addressed to this entity.

hpicfIpv4InterfaceProxyArp.name: hpicfIpv4InterfaceProxyArp
hpicfIpv4InterfaceProxyArp.description: Enables/disables ARP proxy on the interface. If set to 'enabled', the switch will respond on ARP request for IP addresses from other subnets. If set to disabled (the default), the switch will not respond on ARP request for IP addresses from other subnets.

hpicfIpv4InterfaceLocalProxyArp.name: hpicfIpv4InterfaceLocalProxyArp
hpicfIpv4InterfaceLocalProxyArp.description: Enables/disables local ARP proxy on the interface. If set to 'enabled', the switch will respond on ARP request for IP addresses within the local subnet. If set to disabled (the default), the switch will not respond on ARP request for IP addresses within the local subnet.

hpicfIpv4InterfaceBootpGateway.name: hpicfIpv4InterfaceBootpGateway
hpicfIpv4InterfaceBootpGateway.description: This entry will specify the IP address to be used as the BOOTP gateway for this interface. Note that this IP address will be used as the BOOTP gateway only when it is configured as an IP address on this interface. Otherwise, the lowest IP address configured on the interface will be used as the gateway address.

hpicfIpv4InterfaceDirectedBcastFwd.name: hpicfIpv4InterfaceDirectedBcastFwd
hpicfIpv4InterfaceDirectedBcastFwd.description: Enable/disable directed-broadcast forwarding on this interface. When set to default, the global hpicfDBroadcastFwdEnable setting is used. When set to enable, directed-broadcasts are enabled irrespective of the global setting.

hpicfIpClientTrackerEnable.name: hpicfIpClientTrackerEnable
hpicfIpClientTrackerEnable.description: Enable ip client tracking for trusted and untrusted devices.

hpicfIpClientTrackerTrusted.name: hpicfIpClientTrackerTrusted
hpicfIpClientTrackerTrusted.description: Enable ip client tracking for trusted devices.

hpicfIpClientTrackerUntrusted.name: hpicfIpClientTrackerUntrusted
hpicfIpClientTrackerUntrusted.description: Enable ip client tracking for untrusted devices.

hpicfIpv6NDDadAttempts.name: hpicfIpv6NDDadAttempts
hpicfIpv6NDDadAttempts.description: The value in this object indicates the maximum number of neighbor solicitation requests that will be sent while performing duplicate address detection.

hpicfIpv6IcmpErrorInterval.name: hpicfIpv6IcmpErrorInterval
hpicfIpv6IcmpErrorInterval.description: The value in this object indicates the error interval in which the token bucket algorithm places one token in the bucket for ICMPV6 rate limiting.Each token represents the right to send one ICMP error message. Each time an error is sent, it takes a token from the bucket. ICMP will not be allowed to originate an error message if the bucket is empty.

hpicfIpv6IcmpBucketsize.name: hpicfIpv6IcmpBucketsize
hpicfIpv6IcmpBucketsize.description: The value in this object indicates the maximum number of tokens that can be in the bucket.

hpicfIpv6InterfaceTable.name: hpicfIpv6InterfaceTable
hpicfIpv6InterfaceTable.description: This table contains per-interface IPV6 configuration information.

hpicfIpv6InterfaceEntry.name: hpicfIpv6InterfaceEntry
hpicfIpv6InterfaceEntry.description: An entry in the hpicfIpv6InterfaceEntry contains IPV6 interface specific configuration information. This table is indexed by ipv6InterfaceIfIndex.

hpicfIpv6InterfaceDhcpMode.name: hpicfIpv6InterfaceDhcpMode
hpicfIpv6InterfaceDhcpMode.description: Setting this flag to 'dhcpFull' will clear any existing IP address configuration for this interface and will cause the device to use a dynamic method (e.g. DHCP) to obtain its IP configuration and other configuration parameter (such as gateway, time of day, etc...) for this interface. Setting this flag to 'dhcpInform' will allow manual IP address configuration and yet permit other configuration parameters (such as gateway, time of day, etc...) to be obtained from a DHCP server. Setting this flag to 'disabled' will not allow any of the above mentioned two configuration, but interface can have link-local, auto-config and manual ip-address.

hpicfIpv6InterfaceManual.name: hpicfIpv6InterfaceManual
hpicfIpv6InterfaceManual.description: Setting this flag to 'enabled' will allow manual IP address configuration but disallow any DHCP configuration.

hpicfIpv6InterfaceAutoConfig.name: hpicfIpv6InterfaceAutoConfig
hpicfIpv6InterfaceAutoConfig.description: Setting this flag to 'enabled' will allow host to configure automatically from default router. There may be multiple routers and in that scenario switch will add the addresses from all these routers

hpicfIpv6InterfaceDhcpRapidCommit.name: hpicfIpv6InterfaceDhcpRapidCommit
hpicfIpv6InterfaceDhcpRapidCommit.description: Setting this flag to 'enabled' will allow the host to get address and configuration information from the dhcp server rapidly. This flag can be enabled only if the hpicfIpv6InterfaceDhcpMode object is set as dhcpFull. By default this flag is set to disabled.

hpicfIpv6InterfaceDhcpRelay.name: hpicfIpv6InterfaceDhcpRelay
hpicfIpv6InterfaceDhcpRelay.description: This flag indicates whether this interface is dhcp-relay enabled. By default this flag is set to disabled.

hpicfIpv6InterfaceCfgEnableStatus.name: hpicfIpv6InterfaceCfgEnableStatus
hpicfIpv6InterfaceCfgEnableStatus.description: The indication of whether IPv6 is enabled (up) or disabled (down) on this interface. Setting this object to up(1) will enable ipv6 for the given interface.Setting this object to down(2) will disable the ipv6 for the interface only if hpicfIpv6InterfaceDhcpMode, hpicfIpv6InterfaceManual and hpicfIpv6InterfaceAutoConfig are disabled.A get on this object reflects the data saved in a non-volatile storage. Note:To get the current ipv6 status for an interface refer to ipv6InterfaceEnableStatus.

hpicfIpv6InterfaceDadAttempts.name: hpicfIpv6InterfaceDadAttempts
hpicfIpv6InterfaceDadAttempts.description: This object indicates the maximum number of neighbor solicitation requests that will be sent while performing duplicate address detection for this interface. Note: hpicfIpv6NDDadAttempts object's value will be in use for dad attempts for this interface when hpicfIpv6InterfaceDadAttemptsMode is 'global'.

hpicfIpv6InterfaceDadAttemptsMode.name: hpicfIpv6InterfaceDadAttemptsMode
hpicfIpv6InterfaceDadAttemptsMode.description: This object indicates whether the value in hpicfIpv6NDDadAttempts is in use or the value in hpicfIpv6InterfaceDadAttempts is in use for an entry in this table while performing duplicate address detection. A set to 'global' means: - hpicfIpv6NDDadAttempts value will be used for dad attempts. A set to 'perInterface' means: - hpicfIpv6InterfaceDadAttempts value will be used for dad attempts.

hpicfIpv6InterfaceReachableTime.name: hpicfIpv6InterfaceReachableTime
hpicfIpv6InterfaceReachableTime.description: The time a neighbor is considered reachable after receiving a reachability confirmation.

hpicfIpv6InterfaceRetransmitTime.name: hpicfIpv6InterfaceRetransmitTime
hpicfIpv6InterfaceRetransmitTime.description: The time between retransmissions of Neighbor Solicitation messages to a neighbor when resolving the address or when probing the reachability of a neighbor.

hpicfUdpTunnelTable.name: hpicfUdpTunnelTable
hpicfUdpTunnelTable.description: This table contains per interface IPV4 Udp encapsulated tunnel specific configuration information.

hpicfUdpTunnelEntry.name: hpicfUdpTunnelEntry
hpicfUdpTunnelEntry.description: An entry in the hpicfUdpTunnelEntry contains Udp encapsulated tunnel specific configuration information.

hpicfUdpTunnelSrcPort.name: hpicfUdpTunnelSrcPort
hpicfUdpTunnelSrcPort.description: This variable is valid only for the remote mirroring source or destination switch. The value will be ignored otherwise. A value of 0 means that the UDP port is irrelevant for the tunnel type. If this value is non-zero it must be duplicated in the tunnelInetConfigID value (this will ensure that a given UDP port can only be associated once with a given tunnelInetConfigAddressType, tunnelInetConfigLocalAddress, tunnelInetConfigRemoteAddress, tunnelInetConfigEncapsMethod combination).

hpicfUdpTunnelMirrorSessionID.name: hpicfUdpTunnelMirrorSessionID
hpicfUdpTunnelMirrorSessionID.description: This variable is valid only for a remote mirroring switch which interfaces with the source end of the tunnel. The value will be ignored otherwise. A value of 0 means that the mirror session ID is irrelevant for the tunnel type.

hpicfIpAddressTableGroup.name: hpicfIpAddressTableGroup
hpicfIpAddressTableGroup.description: A Collection of objects allowing configuration of an IP address for an interface.

hpicfSwitchIpAddressTableGroup.name: hpicfSwitchIpAddressTableGroup
hpicfSwitchIpAddressTableGroup.description: A Collection of objects providing interfaces addressing information.

hpicfUdpTunnelTableGroup.name: hpicfUdpTunnelTableGroup

hpicfIpv6InterfaceTableGroup.name: hpicfIpv6InterfaceTableGroup

hpicfUdpTunnelMirrorGroup.name: hpicfUdpTunnelMirrorGroup
hpicfUdpTunnelMirrorGroup.description: An object that enables or disables truncation for remote mirroring.

hpicfIpv6NDGroup.name: hpicfIpv6NDGroup
hpicfIpv6NDGroup.description: Objects provided for configuration of ipv6 ND parameters

hpicfIpv4InterfaceTableGroup3.description: A Collection of objects that allows IPV4 interface configuration
